Honda CB150f 2026 Model | Ownership & Review
description:
#hondacb150f #pakistantravel #review #atlashonda #Ahmedbugti 
In this video, I share my complete long-term ownership review of the Honda CB150F, based on real-world riding experience—not just specs on paper.

I start by explaining the exterior design, build quality, and overall look, then move on to the engine performance, followed by my honest experience with fuel average, daily riding, and long-distance touring.

I also discuss:
✔ Honda CB150f Fuel Average
✔ Best Engine oil for Honda CB150f
✔ Turing Tires for Honda CB150f
✔ Top Speed of Honda CB150f
✔ Modifications in Honda CB150f
✔ Tour Ready Honda CB150f
✔ My full touring experience — including my ride all the way to Khunjerab Pass, North Pakistan

After that, I break down the real pros of the Honda CB150F:
– Honda’s brand reliability
– Massive dealership network across Pakistan
– Easy spare parts availability
– Mechanics available everywhere
– Strong resale value

Then I honestly talk about the cons:
– Clunky gearbox feel
– No ABS
– Alloy rims but no company-fitted tubeless tyres
– Rear drum brake instead of disc
– Weak stock headlights

Finally, I sum up the overall performance:
This bike has enough torque, never felt underpowered, and proved itself capable for both city riding and long-distance touring.

If you are planning to buy a Honda CB150F, or already own one, this video will help you make the right decision.
